clusion that ground this landmark work firmly in the present, Setting the People Free is a unique and brilliant account of an extraordinary idea.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 0aDemocracyxHistory. 0aDemocracy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aDunn, John.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2018 Englishz978311060421408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2018z9783110603217oZDB-23-DPH40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691183916zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691183916423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691183916/original  a978-3-11-060421-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DPHb2018